Fix calendar timezone bug: meetings appeared 5 hours early

pywin32's pywintypes.datetime stamps tzinfo=UTC on Outlook appointment
times, but the numeric field values are actually already in LOCAL time
(what Outlook displays). Calling .astimezone() on them did a second
UTC->local shift, which made 4:40 PM meetings appear as 11:40 AM —
pushing them into the "PAST" filter bucket so they silently dropped.

Now trust the raw .year/.month/.hour fields. What Outlook displays is
what we return.

Also: added a refresh=true query param on /calendar/upcoming for the
UI Refresh button (bypasses the 5-min cache), backend logs every
upcoming meeting it returns plus dropped samples to make this class
of bug obvious next time, and the CalendarMonitor now polls every 30s
with a 10s initial delay (was 60s / 2min) so freshly-added meetings
get notifications quickly.

